	 </h3><p><i>Figure 3: A constellation of colours of emitted light from quantum dots. The wavelength of emitted light increases with quantum dots particle size.</i> </p><p>A team of University of California, Riverside researchers discovered that iron oxide (Fe3O4) nanocrystals coated with a charged polymer (polyacrylic acid) forms superparamagnetic colloid solutions in water the colours of which are tunable by application of a magnetic field or variation of its strength (Figure 4).</p><p>
<div class="clear"></div>


