	 </p><p><i>Figure 4: Image shows the solution of iron oxide (Fe3O4) in water changing colour under the influence of a magnetic field, with increasing strength of the field from left to right. </i><i>Photo credit: Yin laboratory, University of California, Riverside </i>(17) <i>. </i> </p><p>
